We forget she wasn’t only abused and kept that part of her life quiet. She also has an autoimmune disease which she needed a fucking kidney transplant for her to save her life. Maybe she didn’t have the time to sort through all of that. At least from personal experience I know you don’t when your body is attacking itself.
She was also young and as Amanda said she may have not recognize her situation as abusive and the trauma kept popping up later in life in ways we don’t get to see until she recognized accepted and healed from it.
I see what Loni was trying to say in the end but it is never a stranger but only the victim/survivor to tell when to they are ready to move on. We don’t ever get to dictate that.
And Justin being married and a born again Cristian does not eradicate the abuse he inflicted on others. The aftermath does not magically disappear. Selena, even if and when she heals from this will never ever be the person she was before she met him. That is life.
So let her express (what may be left of) her pain through music.

snippet.textDisplay: Selena Gomez has every right to talk about her experiences that she had with her relationship with Justin Bieber even though she has never mention his name or has never disrespect him on any interviews that she has ever done. Especially now that her new album "Rare" is out and it's very personal for her with her own experiences that she had. Their relationship lasted off and on for years. It's like her own journal. Questions get asked when she is doing interviews about her new album "Rare" and its related to her overcoming what she experienced herself. She has never spoked about it till now after the help, healing, getting on the right medications, going to therapy and recovery centers to realize that it was a toxic relationship and it wasn't LOVE. That's not including behind the scenes that we didn't get to see. Especially when she stayed away from the spotlight for a long time. As humans it's always easier to judge others until we are there experiencing it ourselves. Whether it's good or bad people are going to talk, give their own opinions. We all heal in different ways that even those experiences, can change us to a whole new person. And she did but it didn't destroy her. Honestly she is just keeping it real with her intentions that other people can learn from it. She doesn't need to use this to sell albums but when she is being asked at interviews, she isn't afraid anymore to answer. She is talented in so many ways that she wouldn't be a celebrity still if that was the case. I salute to her and respect her for keeping it very honest, real and very raw because most celebrities worry to much about keeping their image very clean. We need more people like her.❤
